cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with image memorability and investigates the visual features that make outdoor natural scenes memorable. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end DNN based model for predicting outdoor natural scene memorability. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses deep neural networks to predict memorability scores. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with image memorability and could be useful in designing tourism publicity materials. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper investigates the effectiveness of different features in predicting memorability scores, which could be useful in image retrieval systems.
